SIMPLE: glassy
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Glassy
<hw>Glass"y</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Made of
glass; vitreous; <as>as, a <ex>glassy</ex> substance</as>.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>Resembling glass in its properties, as in
smoothness, brittleness, or transparency; <as>as, a <ex>glassy</ex>
stream; a <ex>glassy</ex> surface; the <ex>glassy</ex>
deep.</as></def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <def>Dull; wanting life or fire; lackluster; -- said of
the eyes.</def> ⟦ldquo⟧In his <xex>glassy</xex> eye.⟦rdquo⟧
<rj><au>Byron.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Glassy feldspar</b></col> <fld>(Min.)</fld>, <cd>a
variety of orthoclase; sanidine.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Glastonbury thorn</ent>⟦br⟧
